      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "An important thing to note about Java Serialization is that it is JVM/version specific and for this, if not other (security) reasons, ill-advised to use as any kind of over-the-socket protocol (cite: Log4J 1.2 abandonment of serialized Java - which in later versions, LogBack ... to JSON k/v String pairs). Within the JVM for things like deep-cloning and other purposes, it is fine otherwise if not slower than native Java methods for data manipulation."
