      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "@DarrellTeague It is not JVM or version specific.  It is specifically designed not to be.  Do you have a reference link to this Log4J problem?  I think it’s far more likely that the intended stability of Java serialization works as designed, and that Log4J developers misunderstood how to use serialization properly."
