      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "@VGR - The comment was out-of-context. Yes, Java Serialization is &#39;standard&#39; across JVMs/versions but ... the point was that two given serialized classes, created from different JVM versions for example, can be incompatible such as if trying to deserialize a Java v8 class in Java v7. That&#39;s the Java-specific reference. The Log4J devs have abandoned the original serialized-object-over-socket implementation. <a href=\"https://cxsecurity.com/issue/WLB-2017040112\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">cxsecurity.com/issue/WLB-2017040112</a>"
