      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "@DarrellTeague That is not true.  I just proved it by serializing an object in Java 11 and reading it in Java 7.  <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/11/docs/specs/serialization/index.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">The serialization specification</a> is a stable specification.  (Perhaps you were thinking of compiled .class files;  it is certainly true that a Java 11 .class file won’t be readable in Java 7, unless the compiler was given <code>-target 7</code> or <code>--release 7</code>.)"
